# Our Research

Our lab's mission to reduce pediatric morbidity and mortality using health services research (HSR) and community-engaged research (CEnR/CBPR) approaches. Our work spans several key areas:

:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="60%"}
## Project 1: Geospatial Analysis

Through collaborations with the UConn GIS Health Lab at Connecticut Children's we investigate the impact of place on pediatric health disparities. 
:::

::: {.column width="40%"}
![](images/noun-gis-1479180.png){width=100px}
:::

::::

:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="60%"}
## Project 2: Low Value Care

Collaborating with Dr. Kimia's NLP tool [DrT](https://documentreviewtools.com/) to investigate predictors of Low Value Care in pediatrics.
:::

::: {.column width="40%"}
![](images/noun-nlp-6950747.png){width=100px}
:::

::::

:::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="60%"}
## Project 3: Health Services Research

Using large datasets, we analyze the impact of social determinants of health on pediatric respiratory morbidity and mortality.
:::

::: {.column width="40%"}
![](images/noun-hospital-1778359.png){width=100px}
:::

::::

# Collaborations

We actively collaborate with researchers from:

- CHA/PHIS
- UCONN GIS Lab at CT Children's
- Connecticut Children's COVID Collaborative